{"title":"New Colnago C68 Allroad blurs road–gravel divide and costs €15,335","link":"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/news/colnago-c68-allroad","date":1677755480000,"content":"<p><a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk\">Cyclist</a><br />\n<a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/news/colnago-c68-allroad\">New Colnago C68 Allroad blurs road–gravel divide and costs €15,335</a></p>\n\n<p>Colnago has released its newest addition to the C-Series, the C68 Allroad, an endurance take on the existing <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/news/colnago-c68\" target=\"_blank\">C68 Road</a>. With the launch of the <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/news/colnago-v4rs\" target=\"_blank\">performance-driven V4Rs</a> last December, the Italian brand’s newest bike is all about day-to-day riding. It’s an <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/buying-guides/best-endurance-road-bikes\" target=\"_blank\">endurance bike</a> that Colnago says aims to cover long days in the saddle over a variety of surfaces.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"970\" height=\"647\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/03/Colnago-C68-Allroad-media-9-970x647.jpg\" alt=\"Colnago C68 Allroad\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/03/Colnago-C68-Allroad-media-9-970x646.jpg 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/03/Colnago-C68-Allroad-media-9-300x200.jpg 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/03/Colnago-C68-Allroad-media-9-768x512.jpg 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/03/Colnago-C68-Allroad-media-9-1536x1024.jpg 1536w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/03/Colnago-C68-Allroad-media-9-2048x1365.jpg 2048w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/03/Colnago-C68-Allroad-media-9-750x500.jpg 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/03/Colnago-C68-Allroad-media-9-1140x760.jpg 1140w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/03/Colnago-C68-Allroad-media-9-465x310.jpg 465w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/03/Colnago-C68-Allroad-media-9-620x413.jpg 620w\" /><figcaption>Colnago</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Colnago already has a fully-fledged <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/what-is-a-gravel-bike\" target=\"_blank\">gravel bike</a> in the form of its <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/reviews/colnago-g3-x-review\" target=\"_blank\">G3-X</a>, and the brand says that the C68 Allroad is ‘not a road bike, nor a gravel bike’ but exists to cover the space in between.</p>\n\n\n<div>\r\n                <div>\r\n                   <div>\r\n                      <div>\r\n                         <h3><span>Related Posts</span></h3>\r\n                      </div>\r\n                      <div>\r\n                         <div>\r\n                            <div>\r\n                            <article>\r\n                    <div>\r\n                       <h3>\r\n                          <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/news/pinarello-f-series-x-series\">Dogma for the people? Pinarello launches F Series racer plus X Series endurance bike</a>\r\n                       </h3>\r\n                    </div>\r\n                 </article><article>\r\n                    <div>\r\n                       <h3>\r\n                          <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/news/colnago-v4rs\">Colnago finally confirms its Prototipo as the new V4Rs all-round race bike</a>\r\n                       </h3>\r\n                    </div>\r\n                 </article><article>\r\n                    <div>\r\n                       <h3>\r\n                          <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/news/colnago-c68\">Colnago’s C68 is more custom, adds 3D-printed Ti lugs and comes with an NFT</a>\r\n                       </h3>\r\n                    </div>\r\n                 </article></div>\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                    <div>\r\n                                    <div>\r\n                                        <div>\r\n                                            <span></span><span></span><span></span>\r\n                                        </div>\r\n                                        <div>\r\n                                            <div>\r\n                                                <div></div>\r\n                                            </div>\r\n                                        </div>\r\n                                        <div>\r\n                                            <div>\r\n                                                <div></div>\r\n                                            </div>\r\n                                        </div>\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                </div>\r\n                                <div>\r\n                                    <div>\r\n                                    <div>\r\n                                        <span></span>\r\n                                        <span></span>\r\n                                        <span></span>\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                </div>\r\n                                \r\n                            </div>\r\n                        </div>\r\n                        </div>\n\n\n<figure><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"970\" height=\"647\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/03/Colnago-C68-Allroad-media-16-970x647.jpg\" alt=\"Colnago C68 Allroad\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/03/Colnago-C68-Allroad-media-16-970x646.jpg 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/03/Colnago-C68-Allroad-media-16-300x200.jpg 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/03/Colnago-C68-Allroad-media-16-768x512.jpg 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/03/Colnago-C68-Allroad-media-16-1536x1024.jpg 1536w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/03/Colnago-C68-Allroad-media-16-2048x1365.jpg 2048w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/03/Colnago-C68-Allroad-media-16-750x500.jpg 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/03/Colnago-C68-Allroad-media-16-1140x760.jpg 1140w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/03/Colnago-C68-Allroad-media-16-465x310.jpg 465w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/03/Colnago-C68-Allroad-media-16-620x413.jpg 620w\" /><figcaption>Colnago</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The Allroad will give riders up to 35mm tyre clearance, up from 32mm on the C68 Road, as well as a more relaxed geometry, which Colnago says should make the riding experience more comfortable when taking the bike off smooth tarmac.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"970\" height=\"647\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/03/Colnago-C68-Allroad-media-14-970x647.jpg\" alt=\"Colnago C68 Allroad\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/03/Colnago-C68-Allroad-media-14-970x646.jpg 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/03/Colnago-C68-Allroad-media-14-300x200.jpg 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/03/Colnago-C68-Allroad-media-14-768x512.jpg 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/03/Colnago-C68-Allroad-media-14-1536x1024.jpg 1536w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/03/Colnago-C68-Allroad-media-14-2048x1365.jpg 2048w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/03/Colnago-C68-Allroad-media-14-750x500.jpg 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/03/Colnago-C68-Allroad-media-14-1140x760.jpg 1140w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/03/Colnago-C68-Allroad-media-14-465x310.jpg 465w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/03/Colnago-C68-Allroad-media-14-620x413.jpg 620w\" /><figcaption>Colnago</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>As such, it is unsurprising that the Allroad has a shorter reach and higher stack than its tarmac-focussed counterpart, but it actually surpasses the G3-X gravel bike in these regards as well, with 10mm longer reach and 23mm higher stack on average.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"970\" height=\"647\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/03/Colnago-C68-Allroad-media-6-970x647.jpg\" alt=\"Colnago C68 Allroad\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/03/Colnago-C68-Allroad-media-6-970x646.jpg 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/03/Colnago-C68-Allroad-media-6-300x200.jpg 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/03/Colnago-C68-Allroad-media-6-768x512.jpg 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/03/Colnago-C68-Allroad-media-6-1536x1024.jpg 1536w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/03/Colnago-C68-Allroad-media-6-2048x1365.jpg 2048w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/03/Colnago-C68-Allroad-media-6-750x500.jpg 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/03/Colnago-C68-Allroad-media-6-1140x760.jpg 1140w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/03/Colnago-C68-Allroad-media-6-465x310.jpg 465w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/03/Colnago-C68-Allroad-media-6-620x413.jpg 620w\" /><figcaption>Colnago</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Colnago says it is keen to reinforce the fact that the Allroad is not an out-and-out off-road machine, highlighting that it is best suited to tarmac, cobblestones, light gravel and other uneven surfaces.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"970\" height=\"647\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/03/Colnago-C68-Allroad-media-15-970x647.jpg\" alt=\"Colnago C68 Allroad\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/03/Colnago-C68-Allroad-media-15-970x646.jpg 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/03/Colnago-C68-Allroad-media-15-300x200.jpg 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/03/Colnago-C68-Allroad-media-15-768x512.jpg 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/03/Colnago-C68-Allroad-media-15-1536x1024.jpg 1536w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/03/Colnago-C68-Allroad-media-15-2048x1365.jpg 2048w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/03/Colnago-C68-Allroad-media-15-750x500.jpg 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/03/Colnago-C68-Allroad-media-15-1140x760.jpg 1140w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/03/Colnago-C68-Allroad-media-15-465x310.jpg 465w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/03/Colnago-C68-Allroad-media-15-620x413.jpg 620w\" /><figcaption>Colnago</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The Allroad frame has also seen some changes, with a squarer, octagonal down tube and reinforced seatstays and chainstays. It’s built from several modular parts, rather than in a monocoque design, and Colnago says it has been refined to create an almost seamless finish.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"970\" height=\"647\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/03/Colnago-C68-Allroad-media-12-970x647.jpg\" alt=\"Colnago C68 Allroad\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/03/Colnago-C68-Allroad-media-12-970x646.jpg 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/03/Colnago-C68-Allroad-media-12-300x200.jpg 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/03/Colnago-C68-Allroad-media-12-768x512.jpg 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/03/Colnago-C68-Allroad-media-12-1536x1024.jpg 1536w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/03/Colnago-C68-Allroad-media-12-2048x1365.jpg 2048w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/03/Colnago-C68-Allroad-media-12-750x500.jpg 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/03/Colnago-C68-Allroad-media-12-1140x760.jpg 1140w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/03/Colnago-C68-Allroad-media-12-465x310.jpg 465w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/03/Colnago-C68-Allroad-media-12-620x413.jpg 620w\" /><figcaption>Colnago</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Available in either a multi-tonal white/black or pure black paintjob, the Allroad will only be sold with <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/buying-guides/buyers-guide-to-road-bike-groupsets\" target=\"_blank\">electronic groupsets</a> from the big three manufacturers, Campagnolo, Shimano and SRAM. A choice of wheels is also on offer, with different options from Enve, Campagnolo, Shimano or Fulcrum.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"970\" height=\"647\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/03/Colnago-C68-Allroad-media-11-970x647.jpg\" alt=\"Colnago C68 Allroad\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/03/Colnago-C68-Allroad-media-11-970x646.jpg 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/03/Colnago-C68-Allroad-media-11-300x200.jpg 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/03/Colnago-C68-Allroad-media-11-768x512.jpg 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/03/Colnago-C68-Allroad-media-11-1536x1024.jpg 1536w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/03/Colnago-C68-Allroad-media-11-2048x1365.jpg 2048w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/03/Colnago-C68-Allroad-media-11-750x500.jpg 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/03/Colnago-C68-Allroad-media-11-1140x760.jpg 1140w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/03/Colnago-C68-Allroad-media-11-465x310.jpg 465w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/03/Colnago-C68-Allroad-media-11-620x413.jpg 620w\" /><figcaption>Colnago</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Never one to put budget before beauty, Colnago has set the RRP for a C68 Allroad, with Dura-Ace Di2 and Shimano C50 wheels, at a whopping €15,335, keeping things very much in the realm of luxury and decadence.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2>Colnago C68 Allroad specs</h2>\n\n\n\n<figure><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"970\" height=\"647\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/03/colnago-c68-allroad-black-970x647.jpg\" alt=\"Colnago C68 Allroad\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/03/colnago-c68-allroad-black-970x646.jpg 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/03/colnago-c68-allroad-black-300x200.jpg 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/03/colnago-c68-allroad-black-768x512.jpg 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/03/colnago-c68-allroad-black-1536x1024.jpg 1536w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/03/colnago-c68-allroad-black-2048x1365.jpg 2048w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/03/colnago-c68-allroad-black-750x500.jpg 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/03/colnago-c68-allroad-black-1140x760.jpg 1140w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/03/colnago-c68-allroad-black-465x310.jpg 465w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/03/colnago-c68-allroad-black-620x413.jpg 620w\" /><figcaption>Colnago</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Groupsets options: </p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li>Campagnolo EPS</li><li>Shimano Dura-Ace Di2</li><li>Shimano Ultegra Di2</li><li>SRAM Red eTap AXS</li><li>SRAM Force eTap AXS</li></ul>\n\n\n\n<figure><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"970\" height=\"647\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/03/colnago-c68-allroad-white-970x647.jpg\" alt=\"Colnago C68 Allroad\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/03/colnago-c68-allroad-white-970x646.jpg 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/03/colnago-c68-allroad-white-300x200.jpg 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/03/colnago-c68-allroad-white-768x512.jpg 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/03/colnago-c68-allroad-white-1536x1024.jpg 1536w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/03/colnago-c68-allroad-white-2048x1365.jpg 2048w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/03/colnago-c68-allroad-white-750x500.jpg 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/03/colnago-c68-allroad-white-1140x760.jpg 1140w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/03/colnago-c68-allroad-white-465x310.jpg 465w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/03/colnago-c68-allroad-white-620x413.jpg 620w\" /><figcaption>Colnago</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Wheelset options: </p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li>Enve WS SES 3.4C</li><li>Campagnolo Bora Ultra WTO 45</li><li>Shimano Dura Ace C50</li><li>Shimano Dura Ace C35</li><li>Fulcrum Wind 400</li><li>Fulcrum Racing 600db</li></ul>\n\n\n\n<p>For more information, go to <a href=\"https://www.colnago.com/bike-product/detail/c68-allroad\" target=\"_blank\">Colnago</a>.</p>\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/news/colnago-c68-allroad\">New Colnago C68 Allroad blurs road–gravel divide and costs €15,335</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk\">Cyclist</a>.</p>","author":"Charlotte Head &#124; Tech Writer","siteTitle":"Cyclist.co.uk","siteHash":"561486e7070fa5351de9318ad0fa26c2a39332acba5fc7c7d1694a01d53d431e","entryHash":"b54acf2d8a9a1b95e1d9c94525ebdc6d3080ae08477027affbf607d1cc2c9780","category":"Cycling"}